DIV Tag (HTML)

The <div> tag is used to define a division or section in an HTML document.

It helps us create containers (sections) that can be styled using CSS.

Syntax:

<div> ... </div>

---

Purpose of <div>

* Used to divide a webpage into sections
* Helps in creating layout
* Works with CSS for styling
* Makes design more organized

---

Page Design Process

1. Determine the requirements of the website
2. Group related information
3. Create a site map
4. Identify key elements for each page
5. Decide layout (arrangement of content)
6. Convert the design into code

---

Summary

* <div> is used for structure (sections)  
* CSS is used for design (styling)
* Both are used together to build webpage layout

